# Project Specific Rules
- NEVER add `declare(strict_types=1);` to any PHP files.
- ALWAYS apply code changes directly to the respective files immediately. Do not just show the code in the response; use file editing tools (write_to_file, replace_file_content) to implement the changes.
- Follow WordPress Coding Standards (WPCS).
- Use Tailwind CSS for styling.
- Use `site_` prefix for new functions and CPTs as per global rules.
